  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.17.1\n\n### What happened?\n\nProviderError: too many arguments, want at most 1\r\n\r\n\r\n\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\nI have encountered the same issue as described in this GitHub thread: https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/issues/4010. Upon referencing the ether.js library, I noticed that they do not pass the second parameter. Here is the link to the code: https://github.com/ethers-io/ethers.js/blob/main/src.ts/providers/provider-jsonrpc.ts#L862. I wonder if we should align with their approach. Currently, it seems that only the mainnet is functioning correctly, while other networks encounter this error.\r\n\r\nhardhat-ethers The location that needs to be modified\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/packages/hardhat-ethers/src/internal/hardhat-ethers-provider.ts#L237\n\n### Search terms\n\n_No response_",
